This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the evaluation of generated text in conversational response tasks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to natural language processing and text generation. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as deep learning models are often used for text generation tasks. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as the paper mentions the use of speech recognition systems in conversational response tasks.
